				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PvP for lower levels<a name="36630"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 1:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You got me killed too much in Unrest:)
<br />

<br />
Seriously...ask yourself these 3 questions
<br />

<br />
1.  Are my offensive/defensive stats maxed(Duel Wield, Offense, Dodge, Defense)?
<br />

<br />
2.  Are my singing and instrument skills maxed to reduce the chances of fizzling during battle?
<br />

<br />
3.  Is my magic resist a minimum of 100?
<br />

<br />

<br />
If you can't answer yes to these 3 questions then you should go grief greenies in FoB...I'm a noob to bards but anyone entering PvP should have those skills/stats maxed for their lvl.
<br />

<br />
Things to try(heh, no idea if they worked yet as I don't have access to many songs at my lvl)---
<br />

<br />
Melee:  Well, unless you can get snare/chant going you're going to have to stick the inkies/scaleheads/Ogurs like the pigs that they are.  They are hands down going to do more damage in melee but you can try wearing them down:
<br />

<br />
Run a damage shield(Psalm of cooling/disease)/Warsong/hymn until you get too low, then back off and chant/heal and go back in when you can...these guys don't have access to healing(accept the monk) so eventually you're going to get them.
<br />

<br />
Wizzies:  Don't get snared:)  Heh, they're best nuke at that lvl range is fire-based I think for wizzies, but whatever it is run a resist song equitable to what they are casting, and just stay in their grill and pummel them to death.
<br />

<br />
Mages:  Most use earth elemental, which is a joke...if your M. Resist is over 80 their root isn't going to stick, just pummel the h*ll out of the mage(fear the pet if you have to) with a resist song running.  Air elementals are a pain in the a$, but high resists should still prevent that stun from occuring.  Shouldn't be too much of a problem...
<br />

<br />
Uh, I think I'll stop here because I most likely don't know what I'm talking about and everything I suggested is most likely wrong anyway:)
<br />

<br />
One thing I will say:  buy some crystalized pumice!  It is a 5 charge nullify magic clicky in case you don't know and is very useful!  You can buy them right outside the kelethin bank for about 16plat...this is almost the first thing I do when I go into battle against anyone...it hopefully gets rid of a rune/AC buff/SoW if you're lucky.
<br />

<br />
Good luck!!!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
