				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PvP for lower levels<a name="38187"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 4 04 7:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Low level PvP with a Bard is easy.  You fight in outdoors zones, for one.  Second, get a LOT of Magic Resist...200+ would be best, but get whatever you can.  Then simply Bellow at people or use whatever attack songs you have from a distance until you get injured...then run away singing your heal song, come back, and keep Bellowing.  You will dominate whole zones of midlevels this way.  They cannot do anything.  You won't be likely to get THAT many kills, but you will control territory, and occasionally there will be someone who doesn't flee in time and then you can try to Snare them once they are weak and alone and open up with your weapons and attack songs until they go down.
<br />

<br />
I wish I could remember the name of the Bard on Tallon Zek that used to do this...he was like level 20, Human, and I remember him dominating the area around the GFay zoneline in BBM...great roleplayer too.</span></td>
